FBIS3-23353 "jptot013__l94034" JPRS-TOT-94-013-L Document Type:JPRS Document Title:Terrorism FOUO 21 March 1994 LATIN AMERICA SURINAME `Liberation Front' Seizes Afobaka Hydroelectric Plant Takes Workers as Hostages PA2203131094 Madrid EFE in Spanish 2343 GMT 21 Mar 94 PA2203131094 Madrid EFE Language: Spanish Article Type:BFN [Text] The Hague, 21 Mar (EFE) -- The Dutch news agency ANP in Paramaribo has reported that members of a guerrilla group seized the hydroelectric plant in Afobaka hours ago and they are currently holding 30 hostages. According to an unidentified spokesman of the group called the "Liberation Front of Suriname," access roads to the hydroelectric plant have been mined in a 7-km radius. The hydroelectric dam supplies energy to the country's capital, located 100 km to the north. According to ANP, the guerrilla group is holding 30 employees of Suralco, a bauxite company, hostage and they are demanding a "decentralization of power" and the resignation of the Surinamese Government.
